{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5751091c-d082-4fcb-b1ae-11c14a03fbe9","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit v2** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit v3** | Same as v2, plus standalone `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report skipped tests in the test results with your reason message visible.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fb2bd4f8-a9c6-4ee3-896d-736357835a61","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax for skipping tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question about .NET test frameworks. Let me check if any of my skills can help here - the `dotnet-test-frameworks` skill seems relevant as it contains \"skip annotations\" information.","outputTokens":370,"requestId":"7C14:1E67:947A1:B5985:69F9436F"},"id":"e24b3d54-0a12-4def-8a5b-159e8fbf9a12","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:10:14.780Z","parentId":"52b6e8b1-910f-4589-92d2-d53860fde857"}
